After the intense search of the homes of the pilot and co-pilot, spotlight is now centered on 53-year-old captain, Zaharie Ahmad Shah and 27-year-old First Officer Fariq Abdul Hamid.Shah is believed to be a strong supporter of Malaysian opposition leader Anwar Ibrahim. The plane went missing just one day after the Malaysian politician was convicted of sodomy and sentenced to five years in prison.After raiding his home in Kuala Lumpur suburbs, police found a self-made aviation simulator. His personal computer was not in his house and police suspected that it's on the plane.The two did not ask to fly together, according to Malaysian Minister of Transport Hishammuddin Hussein on Sunday's press conference.